{
  "texts": [
    "Chain of Thought.",
    "Recently, the use of rationales generated by LLMs has become a popular trend, setting itself apart from the traditional reliance on human-generated rationales [21,26].",
    "Previously, human rationales have been used for model regularization [50], as additional inputs for predictions [48], and to improve model performance [6,15,20,27,46,77,80,81].",
    "They also serve as gold standard labels for generating similar rationales to enhance interpretability [14,45,63,73].",
    "However, the cost of human rationales limits their widespread use."
  ]
}